      "Text": "[llm] system: %buildStepPrompt%\n        user: %step.Serialize.Builder%\n        scheme: {\n                errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                actions: [{module: string, action: string, parameters?: [{name: string, value?: object, type?: string}], return?: [{name: string}],\n                    errors?: [{key: string, message: string}],\n                    warnings?: [{key: string, message: string}]}]\n                }\n        on error call HandleBuildStepFailure\n        write to %result%",
      "Comment": null,
      "ModuleType": "PLang.Modules.LlmModule",
      "Name": "call_llm_with_step_prompt_and_handle_response",
      "Description": "Send the system prompt stored in %buildStepPrompt% and the user prompt stored in %step.Serialize.Builder% to the LLM module. The expected response should conform to a specified JSON schema including errors, warnings, and actions with detailed parameters. If an error occurs during this call, the step should invoke the HandleBuildStepFailure handler. The final response is written to the %result% variable for further processing.",
